o compare is difficult.<br>
<br>
By &quot;passive&quot;, I basically mean &quot;not as active as cannabalize or mana robes&quot;.  The lack of these two does impact the validity of this work.<br>
<br>
Here is how each class stacks up mana regen wise:<br>
Groups:<br>
Necro @ 101 / tick<br>
Enchanter @ 89 / tick (eating caster NPCs)<br>
Wizard @ 83 / tick<br>
Mage @ 78 / tick<br>
Druid @ 75 / tick<br>
Enchanter @ 74 / tick (if no caster NPCs to eat)<br>
Cleric @ 71 / tick<br>
Shaman @ 63 / tick<br>
<br>
Raids:<br>
Necro @ 148 / tick<br>
Wizard @ 133 / tick<br>
Enchanter @ 131 / tick (eating caster NPCs)<br>
Druid @ 118 / tick<br>
Mage @ 116 / tick<br>
Enchanter @ 116 / tick (if no casters NPCs to eat)<br>
Cleric @ 114 / tick<br>
Shaman @ 114 / tick<br>
<br>
Shamans have a massive means of &quot;active&quot; mana regen via cannabalization.  Given that a shaman can manage another 40 to 60 mana/tick on top of the above values, they are rather misrepresented.<br>
<br>
Mages have a similar, if more crippling, ability to pet cannabalize for massive mana regen.<br>
<br>
Mod rods are factored into mage group and everyone's raid mana regen.  To use these perfectly, it requires some effort on the part of the player.  On raids, nobody is paying for the mod rods.<br>
<br>
9 points of a wizards mana regen is via harvest spells.  These are once very 8 to 10 minute &quot;active&quot; mana regen, passive enough for my tastes.<br>
<br>
20 pts of an Enchanters mana regen requires perfect mana management (gather mana) for 5 of it, and 15 pts requires a caster mob always in camp and some timing skills.<br>
<br>
Necros have to lifetap to maintain that level of mana regen.<br>
<br>
How the above values where worked out:<br>
<br>
Common:<br>
26 mana/tick from medding/horse and being L 65.<br>
15 mana/tick from FT<br>
3 mana/tick from MC<br>
5 mana/tick from KHF<br>
KEI is 14/tick, and is almost always up on high level characters.<br>
<br>
Baseline total: 63 mana/tick<br>
<br>
Common Buffs:<br>
Enchanter in group/raid gives +4 mana/tick, above and beyond KEI.<br>
<br>
BST in group gives +9 mana/tick.  +8 mana/tick for wizards (they have to swap Force Shield for Epic).<br>
<br>
A Mage in group/raid can give +9 mana/tick, in exchange for 2 mana/tick from the mage, and a touch of healing or regen.<br>
<br>
A Bard in group/raid can give +21 mana/tick<br>
<br>
Druids can buff others with Po9, for +8 mana/tick.  Only +2 mana/tick for mages and 0 for clerics, however.<br>
<br>
So, at a raid with maxed out buffs, we end up with another 51 mana per tick for most classes, 50 for wizards, and 45 for mages and 43 for clerics.<br>
<br>
Class specific mana regen.<br>
<br>
Wizards:<br>
Allegent Familliar: 8 mana/tick<br>
HoD: 6 mana/tick<br>
Harvest: 3 mana/tick<br>
Epic: 3 mana/tick (or Force Shield for 1 less)<br>
<br>
Total: +20 mana/tick class specific<br>
So, in groups, 83/tick, and on raids 133 mana/tick<br>
<br>
Necros:<br>
UberLich: 50 mana/tick, -14/18 for no KEI/VoQ<br>
Force Shield: 2 mana/tick<br>
<br>
Total: +38 normal/+34 raid<br>
So, in groups, 101 mana/tick, and on raids 148 mana/tick<br>
<br>
Enchanter:<br>
Scryer's Tresspass: 15 mana/tick (requires a caster target)<br>
Gather mana (hasted x3): 5 mana/tick<br>
Shield of Auras for +2 mana/tick.<br>
<br>
ToT and WM are barely ever worth it at this level of play.  Against L 50 caster mobs, you could pull off another 20 mana/tick using these two spells.<br>
<br>
Note both of the above are extremely difficult to use at full efficiency.<br>
<br>
VoQ gives +4 in xp groups (is assumed on raids)<br>
<br>
Total: +26 normal/+22 raid<br>
So, in groups, 89 mana/tick, and 136 on raids<br>
<br>
Mage:<br>
Self mod rodding gives 7/tick in an xp group.<br>
Self armor buff is +6/tick<br>
Shield of Auras for +2 mana/tick.<br>
<br>
Total: +15<br>
So in groups, 78 mana/tick and 116 on raids<br>
<br>
Druids:<br>
In groups, Po9 buffing ability gives 8 mana/tick.<br>
Self buff of 4 mana/tick as well<br>
<br>
Total: +12 normal, +4 raids<br>
75 mana/tick in groups, 118 on raids<br>
<br>
Clerics:<br>
8 mana/tick in groups via self buff, does not stack with Po9<br>
<br>
Total: +8<br>
71 mana/tick in groups, 114 on raids<br>
<br>
Shamans:<br>
no passive mana regen.<br>
<br>
63 mana/tick in groups, 114 on raids<br>
<br>
