<br>
However, there is a difference -- you need to go nearly or completely oom precicely every 100 minutes, and time it perfectly, to use gather mana at full efficiency.  You &quot;just&quot; need to time mod rods.<br>
<br>
Wouldn't using mod rods at near 7 mana per tick just be a matter of an egg timer going DING every 5 minutes?  With the new, more efficient, rods, you can regen the damage a mod rod does before you are allowed to use it again (with regen 3 or mage self buffage or sitting most of the time).<br>
<br>
Rod mana regen isn't as passive or as good as a stacking buff.  Quantifying this difference is difficult, so I'm ignoring it.<br>
