 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wybart>Wybart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/21/03 7:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comparative &quot;Passive&quot; Mana Regen -- NonMelee</span><hr size=1> The part about having to time Gather Mana perfectly is not really about clicking the button or being busy at the time it pops, like with a mod rod. It is that you have to prepare yourself to go completely oom right when the button pops, to maximixe efficientcy. Needless to say, this is pretty risky, and given that enchanters generally have to stay above ca. 40%, I dont know anyone who uses it this way. It seems wrong to include if you dont also include canni, which *is* being used as mana regen.<br>
<br>
Also a correction: You cannot stack WM with Scryers. So WM is out. And ToT returns close to no mana on 57+ mobs (we still dont know if that is a bug or intentional). At the most this would be FT2 (pushing it). And both spells need a devoted spellslot each due to recast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/21/03 11:42 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comparative &quot;Passive&quot; Mana Regen -- NonMelee</span><hr size=1> Wybert, WM and ST don't stack, but they have long recast times and short durations.  You can keep one or the other up at all times, and gain full mana regen from both spells.<br>
<br>
I advise against it, which is why I didn't factor WM or ToT into enchanter mana regen.  Yes, they can squeeze something like 2 mana per tick out of WM, and a huge amount via ToT on green mobs.<br>
<br>
I'm not also counting cannabalization.<br>
<br>
C5 gives 40 mana per tick net (3 minute reuse time right?).<br>
<br>
Chain casting C4 gives 82 mana per tick (including human recovery time).<br>
<br>
This costs 148 hp per tick for C4 and 64 hp per tick for C5.<br>
<br>
So, for -212 hp/tick they can gain 122 extra mana per tick.  With SCRM, 20% mana preservation focus (random, so 10%), spec alt and SCM3, it costs 22 mana per tick to keep quintessence perma-up all the time.  This reduces your C4 abilities by 16% (casting topor means not casting C4).<br>
<br>
So, a shaman can actively generate over 108 mana per tick using cannabalization, but this requries chain casting.  Mages can do similar active mana regen via pet cannabalization.<br>
<br>
Do I put +108 on the shaman, and +some simularly obscene number for mages?  Or do I only factor in C5?<br>
<br>
My note that these tactics are availiable is enough.  This is passive mana regen, spells that don't require actively compensating or chain casting to use.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wybart>Wybart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comparative &quot;Passive&quot; Mana Regen -- NonMelee</span><hr size=1> You are right Laeyakk, I didnt even concider interchangeing casting WM and Scryeers, but it is possible. It is just so absurd in practice. My only objection really is that this is so theoretical that you get a scewed picture of reality. And being that it is posted in &quot;Caster balance&quot; I figured that is what you were trying to show. It looks like shamans have the crappiest regen of all, and enchanter are pretty well off. Reality is that shamans have (in my opinion) by far the best regen. As an enchanter at 65 I get scryers mana back at very best 50% of the time (average maybe 10% of playing time), WM/ToT mana never. A shield of Auras is given to all int casters, and Gather mana is used as passiv regen. I'd have to spend an absolute minimum of 32 AA's to get it that way as well.<br>
<br>
I agree that it is hard to put a number on shaman canni, but completely excluding it just seems so wrong concidering the absurd situation other classes have to be in to get the posted number. But if you know the game and can read between the lines I think its a good overview. <p><B><I><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29310>Wybart</I></B></A>
<BR>Enchanter Lv 65<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/24/03 12:40 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comparative &quot;Passive&quot; Mana Regen -- NonMelee</span><hr size=1> I only gave Shielf of Auras to Mages and Enchanters.  It doesn't stack with force shield/wizard epic, which gives as much or more mana regen.<br>
<br>
And yes, I used max AA and max gear for my numbers.<br>
<br>
Shaman and Mage cannibalization isn't factored in.  I mentioned it right below the numbers.  I couldn't turn it into a good number, so that is the best I can do.<br>
<br>
It wasn't excluded, it was placed in an appendix.<br>
<br>
Spikey mana regen has problems for every class.  Mod rods, harvests, and GM all have advantages and disadvantages over other forms of mana regen.  In 5 minutes, an enchanter can nuke to OOM, GM, then start nuking again.  Valueing it at mana/time seems a reasonable comprimise, I could exclude it (which is a bad idea) or place it in a seperate table I guess.<br>
<br>
So, I included it, and added a comment at the end of the table.  =p<br>
<br>
The addition of 2 entries for an enchanter should deal with the ST problem.<br>
<br>
Possibly I should add &quot;active mana regen&quot; in yet another table.  Anyone have numbers for peak pet cannibalization rates, with some backing?<br>
